Contents.Description: A baby dragon left this behind.
Handed down to the shadows when, once again, he hand built a new one. Unique from the chips up, for when the chips are down.
This weapon was unfortunately lost by its previous owner, luckily found by ever watchful Kender Fibi.
Katana forged in ancient japan.
This ranged weapon of Keriomo's was often considered a blessing, as the dwarf would use rubber bullets or tranquilizer darts instead of lethal ammunition.
Wrought in the aseptic fires of an autoclave out of the tears of a thousand surgeons
A high quality focus brought into countless battles that has proven invaluable.
There is only The Pack, protect it and meet all threats to it with swift and unrelenting violence. Leave no foe behind.
Just when it appears that all hope is lost, this armor give it's wearer a second chance.
Find your center and find your Qi. Find your Qi and the world opens to you.
Hoi Chummers!  Have a great Day!
When Madevil started out as a Shadowrunner, he had one supporter and friend: Strike-None. It has served us well.
The focus of the mage Heartborne of the 4th World. He has the fortune or misfortune to be living over and over again, and is searching for his lost treasures.
Has used this item in his tireless search for secret corp info to broadcast to the masses. DOWN WITH THE CORPS!!!!!
In the shadows it's always someone's last chance. Yours or someone else's, make sure it's not yours.
This katana still remembers the martial prowess of its former mistress.
famously used this combat focus to wipe out a complete squad of Aztechnology security guards
As he slagged the spider's brain with biofeedback he proved one thing - even in the matrix a troll still prefers to smash things.
Paralyzed at birth Dakoi grew up imagining he was a warrior in the Games. This program he developed is fashioned after his 20th century vid hero.
Used during sea battles in the Caribbean...
This is golden rear has been modified by MOM to be used for all your armoring needs!
Sure Chummer, with magic everything is theoretically possible!
This hardplast replica firearm was McDougal's favorite ranged weapon in the early 2070's. Using custom AR, he loved to disguise it as a colorful toy gun.
crafted by Argol to be initiated as archmage
This weapon has been carried by several great warlords of the Arabian Peninsular and North Africa, bringing them glory and riches.
Crafted by master Orc hacker Sebawufu for his friend Keevan so he would always be able to do simple math quickly.
Any armor that keeps me from takin' the big dirtnap is lucky enough for me... Crunch~
Phaid took a gamble on this
This weapon features a bound fire elemental.  The weapon always feels warm to the touch and has been said to burn would be thieves.
This weapon was used by Dwarven Rigger  Jobu to get revenge for his fallen runners, Now does someone needs to deal revenge for him?
This armor was designed by Lt. Eccher from Milspec components and reinforced with Nanite technology for the strongest durability available.
Pain will be your last memory
When you absolutely need to stop something
Vinak, Xoknath's father, died defending the tribe using this weapon. His son continues to do so in the today streets.
It's an icepick!  How deadly can it be?
This is what a doc need to wear!
I use this whenever I need to adjust someone's attitude a little bit... or a lot.
There are some things in the darkness that put fear in the bravest man.
Only a high level Adept can unlock and safely harness the boundless energy of this chi gem.
This jesters mask wouldn't seem appropriate for any sane runner. But where is the fun in that?
Stolen by a notorious cat burglar, she kept it as a trophy since acquiring it nearly cost her life.
Mr Black's Trenchcoat flared open, revealing enough weaponry to outfit a small separatist uprising.
An overwhelming rush of conflicting emotions overtake you every time you wield this wicked masterpiece.  The end brings yet another pile of steaming viscera.
The weapon clearly displays the wear of abundant use, no doubt from all the enemies Shike cut down with it.
Left as a gift to Rigger's when he went dark, Riskbreaker gives its user the one thing most important thing to Riggers: Control
A good decker manages to steal your data without being detected, yet still manages to make you feel like it was deeply personal.
A custom device crafted by a master, but modified by a reckless troll. The end result is an advanced, but wonky peace of tech.
Wishing you love, luck, health and happiness on your birthday. I hope this armor will keep you safe in the shadow. With love Daddy.
this item has inlaid runes which throb with sickly green energy, giving you the uneasy feeling of being watched
Want an even bigger badaBOOM? Try this BOOMstick! *flex* (BOOM!)
To bring death upon all foes
Sometimes you need to convince people that everything worked as planned. And sometimes you need to get rid of them before they can tell anybody that it didn't!
Picked up from the dead hands of Oyabun Hanzo Shotozumi's from the Shotozumi-gumi
Once worn by a great runner that sadly thought that making a deal with a dragon was a smart idea.
Rebuilt to correct the latency in the stock neural interface.
A note in a pocket: "1730: Meet with Mr. Johnson 1815: Pick up daughters from dance recital. 1900: Dinner. 2000: Bedtime for-" The rest is too burnt to read.
An early Focus developed by the Mage Aelred soon after the return of magic.
Curious... What does this do? Yeah I think I'll be taking that... and that... and that..
This has gotten me out of a few tight scrapes over the years, may it do the same for you.
Do your best to do good, but remember that sometimes good isn't good enough.
Qualestor: vampire destroyed in 2047, oddly parts of his skull still contain some of his magical energy.
Forged from the toenail of an Elder Dragon it will slice and dice while your victim stares in awe at its beauty.
This armor was crafted by Melkor by fusing a portion of his own mind into the metals.
A custom job -- old and beat-up but still serviceable.  Keep it out of sight - someone's probably looking for it.
reward if found
The hacker and smuggler ran anywhere from Japan over Seattle to Aztlan, but had to abandon ship on occasion. His waterproof equipment could mostly be recovered.
Lost to history. Found when greatly needed.
One of many early prototypes of a personal magical focus. An inscription reads: "Model #13 - Property of Dr. Vincent A. Belmont. If found, return to..."
He used it once and it was a nightmare...
If you clear your mind you might hear the great rustling of the cosmos.
Surplus armor they said. Combat ready they said. Hasnt seen a battle they said! Without my work this would just be scrap!!
Whoever gets this, take it, sell it, use it, I don't give a drek anymore. Finally saved enough creds to retire in comfort. I won't be needing this. Good luck.
You hold in your hands one of the most advanced pieces of arcane equipment ever to be made. Consider yourself lucky.
This weapon was once owned by the legendary runner LosLobos. The inscription on the handle reads, "When a wolf calls out the pack responds."
This item appears to have been customised using archaic parts, but somehow performs up to the standards of the day...perhaps even better.
Sometimes all you have left is your Edge.
When loves goes bad it can leave a hole in your heart that may never heal, especially when there are weapons like this involved.
Owner destroyed city blocks with the weapon of this magnitude, could only be controlled by liberal amounts of soju.
RIP Devon Daugherty
Sometimes you need to bring a little more heat to a fire.
It worked for him well enough. And it wasn't always for something malevolent. Maybe.
Not everything in the matrix is swift and painless - some things just rot away bit by bit.
A stiff drink can be a reward for a hard day or a celebration for a job well done. Either way, it's always better on the rocks.
Two spells are better than one. - Salfron
Wielded in memory of a life once lost.
Originally used by the Tir Tairngire Outlaw during his smuggling runs over the border. The weapon saved his life after he ran afoul of a Border Patrol Hellhound
Lost since the 4th age, this relic resurfaced with the coming of Haley's comet.
Powered by the magic of Uluru and tested at Thunderdome!
Made this in my mom's basement after a long night of gaming, warm beer, and cold snail pizza.
Rascal never wanted to stand out from the crowd. But he always wanted to know what was going on.
Cearbhall  Dlaigh was the last owner of this artefact. Its origin and meaning remain unclear.
Weapon once wielded by Warrick "Wardog" Sutton, a famous troll street samurai from the California Free State
This is an artefact of the Iroquois Peoples May it help guide you with the spirt world.
Hoi from the MKE node. Don't forget to compensate for latency chummer lest you get dumped.
For those times when you need military-grade virtual support
A legacy set of toolkits passed down from generations, before passing of Daddy to enable Vittra to gain unrestricted entry to anywhere.
Developed at Renraku and designed to bypass any IC it encounters, it was stolen before it was fully tested.
Equality is just a swing away.
Personal melee weapon of Shaynei Voidson, in combat it hums generating feelings of doom and loss to opponents of the person who bonds with this weapon.
Death Beguiles us All
It's been said that God plays with loaded dice...just learning from the master.
God doesn't play dice, but likes a good barbeque.
Formerly belonging to Eiji Yamashita, owner of a lore shop, who said that this weapon would 'grant the gift of wisdom to those who tried to cross him'.
Crafted by himself as a part of a set of tools to achieve objectives underhandedly.
This armor piece was crafted by Nicole Jansen, who sought to save the souls of those that killed her husband... by freeing them from their mortal bodies.
When you need to keep things real...
Liam "Specter" O'shaughnessy forged this focus from his old police badge, turning it from a symbol of authority into a weapon against it.
Carved from an ancient oak
Each has his place to stand, where he knows where he belongs in the scheme of things and what he may achieve. Destroy the place and you destroy the person.
This weapon has a tragic past. Its previous owners finding it after great loss have wielded its power to seek justice and retribution.
One of the few pieces of code written by Lazarus that is now in other people's hands
Used to defend himself and mates versus a wyrm. Never poke one in the eye.
The spirits of the primordial forests sing from these components, creating a symphony of vibrations ready to serve your will.
Citizens Unite!
When up is down and left is right, blood shall warm the coldest night.
Be Aware that everything around you is a lie. Go to sleep knowing you will die.
Still legal in one municipality. Handle with care, do not taunt Over-Volter. Do not use if casing is cracked/leaking. You assume all risks & damages from use.
Recovered from Saeder-Krupp's headquarters in a blackened state after a diplomatic mission gone awry. The status of its previous owner is unknown.
The previous owner modified this item to hack into electronics by simply turning them off and then on again. Also there is a large folder named 'PRON'.
Some pray for riches or gold, I pray for blood and souls.
Twitch made this for me. It might not be the best, but it's one of a kind.
A True Master of Gun Kata...
Found in the Acheron river dropped by mighty Thanatos himself!
Ancient and new at the same time. None know how old or where it comes from. But all owners can agree it has power over the dead and the dying.
From the True North strong and free it stands on guard for thee!
Charismatic leader and astute tactician Carl "Mack" McDowell designed this to help him coordinate his team's actions on runs.
After settling the score with a known dragon for its unsavory slave-trade, Simon borrowed it but felt it could now be put a to better use
A mistress in blood red armour, Excrutia cut a swath through the shadows with this. This is now the vessel of Excrutia's hunger, and it will not be sated.
This old thing has been kicking around my apartment as a coaster for a while. What do you mean, what's a coaster? Philistine!
As this is the slim version do NOT move to fast.
Used in seventeen successful shadowruns requiring a live decker presence (Scottsdale's specialty)... of eighteen.
Desmi's vital essence, a foul green vapor, blew out over the sea. Mingling with the waves, condensed to become a green pearl which sank to the ocean floor.
Brought to you from a Trouper vault deep in the Keweenaw frozen in ice.
This Item was created from Fastjack
Originally crafted as a gift from a humble man for his patron goddess. Please treat it well - one day, Skuld will return for it.
RODENTO ERGO SUM
Leader of Good Times Freebooters personal weapon. X marks the spot either by loot or daka daka.
Karma has a way to keep things in balance.  Coop learned this the hard way after a great run.
It used to be a stylish jacket, five or six patches ago. Still, it looks durable enough.
When you lift the lid on this, you wish you had never even looked.
Two in the chest one in the head, now THAT'S what I call Insurance.
The supreme art of war is to subdue the enemy without fighting. -Sun Tzu
And his countenance was like lightning, and his raiment white as snow.
A piece of ATROM's spirit will live forever in this item. ATROM's spirit is restless and yearning for freedom. This is a strong source of power to be unleashed.
Damian travelled the world to find the strongest fire magic to imbue his weapon with the power as if from earth's magma it's self so he could melt his enemies!
Shadows wreathe your hands as you pull mana through the focus.
Untested labyrinthine prototype. Use at your own risk. Don't panic. The Matrix is a rats maze.
HROATH G'BLON BRACK ROTHAN
Hey! Listen
Great surprises can be for good or for evil... and for its bearer usually comes in double.
An heirloom created by Angel L. Sanchez Sr.  It has been passed down to the first born of each new generation of Sanchez.
The final spell forced through this talisman fried both the mage and the death squad cornering his team. His scream of rage echoes through it still.
Rumored to have been manufactured by legendary weapons smith Frederik for his friend Gus as payment to hunt down the murderers of his wife.
Famous weapon from the hoard of Dunklezahn. If it is pulled, the blade starts to burn in blue fire.
It served him well.
When things get tough, take the game to a whole new level.
Something peaceful about pulling the trigger and a soft THUNK is all you hear, no noise, no signals, just you, your target, and a dozen arrows
The troll shaman who commissioned this weapon had it modified to take a heavier charge yet still have a smooth action to follow through for a controlled pair.
Don't mind the case, it's vintage. A shiny chrome deck tells other runners you have more nuyen than sense.
Custom configured by the underground legend Fail_Condition, this item is ugly on the outside but perfection on the inside.
No matter who he looked like that day, Echo was always suave. Hell he made this armor look good. Maybe some of his suaveness will rub off on you. Or maybe not.
Once used by the last of the freelance hackers and Greatest swordfighter in the world.
HudsoNet specialized in software and hardware development of bleeding edge attack and defence solutions for serious Matrix users.
Wielded by the SINner-turned-Scarlet Pimpernel in his final standoff. That is, if you believe the rumors.
Nightly Builds are run at 0300Z. They are often buggy, but contain the latest features and fixes.
It's hopefully stable, despite being overclocked to a potentially dangerous level.
Hagan went to great lengths to obscure as much of his past as he could.
Today is a good day to die
What time is it?
Emblazoned with the word 'SpecialT', no one knows where these mysterious relics originated or what the name means...
Hangman, enemy of Evo, a mage who brutally made a runner cut their own legs off with their monofilament whip, earning the new alias "Legs"
Magic is most effective when you allow it to change yourself as well as the world around you.
One of five items supposedly looted from a long-lost shrine. Rumors claim whoever collects all five relics will be visited by the spirit of a great warrior.
Recovered from the ice cold cave of Argyle
Always finish off with a head shot
Athrun was an elite hacker. Corperations paid top dollar for him. Until he stayed in too long and fried his brain. Some say he is still in the net...
I give cancer. I kill Jack.
Every now and then one of these custom made weapons pops up all bearing the same maker's mark. More than a few have been linked to high profile assassinations.
Can you see the Darkness approaching
Good music takes you on a journey.  Bad music is like a pothole on that journey.  I don't like potholes.
Need to get in fast and easy. Sleaze your way through any security.
I bought it for self-defence, I didn't know it would do THAT!
Said to have been created in a wager for someone's soul before the first crash, it's still considered a drek hot piece of gear!
This SMG is the twin to Licktoren's Favorite weapon, his other SMG.
What's this...? Did you just bring me soykaf when I asked for coffee?!? Is that what just happened??!?
It's sturdier than it looks...really.
A weapon of some infamy, it was used as a signature by a Balkans based hitter using the name Vilesh who liked to get close and personal before taking a memento.
Imbued with almost mystical-like qualities, this piece of tech allows it's user to dive deeper and faster, reaching the most shadowy corners of The Matrix.
This item was crafted by Anrion. It may seem to be not that powerful, but knowing about the truth may turn out to be more valuable than having a big weapon.
Remember my ancestor? Cave of Caerbannog ring any bells...?
It was crafted near a volcano in Auvergne in France....
This weapon provides the wielder an advantage to parry and dodge attacks split seconds before they happen.
Gas passer of the Northwest Territories
Flynn designed it. Jones used it. Cereal killer smashed it. Zedd repaired it.
Given to the decker Prowler through the Will of Dunkelzahn, lost to him during Crash 2.0
A stone's sorrow is immortal. May its power lengthen the time of your own despair.
Wielding this was the best thing ever... really!
As if to honor his Fifth World namesake, Sean "Prospero" von Bayern has seemingly done his best to perfect the role of an entitled and bitter old man.
Catori is a cat adept who runs with First Nations in Seattle. She changes armor like she changes outfits, which is why you have this now.
The only solution against any pain!
Like being a Troll. - TrogTuff Armorware slogan.  TrogTuff Corp marketed these as being tough as Troll hide.  Rumors claim that it was made from Troll hide.
C0d3Wr3ck wasn't happy bricking devices one at a time. Using this custom prog he was able to duplicate a single matrix attack action on a second target.
Special Mod version of the gun that enables the user to inflict fatal damage to the target.
Custom built sniper rifle. The target will never see it coming, and never see anything again.  89 notches on the stock...and a 90th made by the new owner.
It might be shooting buckshot, but the only thing it makes is edible for cats and rats.
The only thing better than "State of the Art" is "Bleeding Edge".  This is beyond even that.
When this item is used it fills the user with a sense of elation and superiority. You know you should not use it, but it is hard to stop.
Power corrupts. Absolute power corrupts absolutely. But it rocks absolutely, too.
When everyone around you is losing their head, this item has always had a calming and focusing effect for that all important hack job...at least for the owner!
Developed by V'Lyn Technix for corporate black-ops teams, a number have been acquired by less reputable entities.
Jim Bean built the original Bean Machine as a analogue phone line, over the years it has received numerous upgrades. This was once part of that network.
It's clobberin' time!
This weapon was modified from a concept design of an anti-material rifle.  Suffice to say, it works well against squishy things too.
Always look on the bright side of life.
Hoi chummer! If you have this weapon the owner has been tagged. Take good care of her - shes smarter than you. And remember: shoot now and ask questions later.
When you need to send some long-range "love" to that special someone...
[audio chip is embedded in the handle]: Frag! They're coming! Motherfragging insect spirits! The Brotherhood is a front! Stay away!
Skuld, the youngest Valkyrie, with her two sisters Uror and Veroandi, shall decide your fate.
Meticulously crafted from the finest materiel, this focus shows great care was taken to produce a quality item
A mixture of Japanese dedication and native
Just another way to confuse us more.
An old scribbled paper tells the reader, to better look out, too much given joy could mean, your soul wants join hell sooner, than you intended too.
When your luck is this bad, a reliable gun is its own lucky charm.
Used in several aggressive negotiations. Just pull trigger.
The mighty TUNG was a powerful half-orc barbarian.  His rage in battle was matched only by his love for his friends.
He tried to defend himself with this, but the runners that took him down had something bigger. Don't they always? His career in politics is now at an end.
Crazy? You haven't seen crazy!!! After this you will be as mad as me!!!
Don't plug it in! You'll be sorry.
When inspected in AR, a small tag appears next to the weapon: "Don't fragging lose this one, too!!" (the tag is written in comic-sans and blinks annoyingly)
stolen by Cpl Mclean and used to kill the Sgt in his sleep. Purse's essence poured into the weapon, with the sole ambition of taking his revenge.
Never taunt an Ambermage:"What are you going to do about it?!"
A Cat shaman
This potent focus was a Casavant family heirloom, passed down through the ages.  The hide used to bind it is as mysterious as its contents.
With its constant shapechanging, you aren't sure what it actually looks like. But the previous owner must have been small, but skilled in illusion and charming.
I powerful item used against horrors during the last cycle. It used to control and repel spirits. Especially against Toxic spirits.
Mojay trusted a dragon.  Alas, he is no more.
AYBABTU
Owned by the Street Samurai this automatic weapon has survived firefights all over Seattle
A tool of the truly ambitious. There's no better way to leave your mark on the world.
A lucky trinket from Chicago.
A rod of copper topped with a Star Saphire, Ravenhull used this to help focus his abilities.
Forged for Primarch in payment for rescuing a shaman and wizard. The design is often copied, but never rivals the original.
For some reason, "The birdie is innocent" has been scrawled into this item.
May this stylized hatchet protect you and yours as it has me and mine.
A highly-customized weapon formerly owned by a shadowrunner-assassin known as "Lash". Last seen in the Seattle area, her current whereabouts are unknown.
Passed down from generations upon generations only to end up in your hands.
Large divots and battle damage has cut this bait armor down to size, as if a crab had thrown it around like a mere pebble.

Created by the enchanters of the Arch Overseers for the combat mage Amanrahin Samshaidar during their quest for dominance over their rivals.
Software written by Fang, a snarky changeling Technomancer disguising himself as a mundane hacker. He's not arrogant, honest!
On his 18th birthday Questor received a box containing a special item, pulsing with mysterious energy: The focus of his mother. A mother he never met.
Morphed from his first custom hacking program software, it has become a project he keeps up to date to keep himself ahead of the curve.
The edge one wields can define them, but it need not confine them.  Don't be afraid to grow, for change is how we survive.
Blackbeard was a decker of great renown who suddenly vanished from one day to the next. It's unknown what happened to him.
The lengthy Odachi sword serves its master effectively, wielded with one or two hands.
This gun was pried from Cylon's cold dead hand with the slide locked back and magazine empty of course!
Why just face death, when you can wrap yourself in it?
Handle with care last owner forgot to do so.
Made from pure resonance the Technomancer Crow programmed this device to influence military grade matrix security. Let's hope it works better for you than him!
Keep out of reach of children
This is why Bill has half a head.
Property of the infamous part-decker part-spider, his possessions reeks of his signature paranoia with arrays of booby traps and hidden weapon compartments.
When drawn, apply blood before re-sheathing
Derek Dark, ill reputed corporate assassin, has left this piece of hardware in the shadows for you to use... for now he will reclaim it sooner than you think
When you were born, you cried and the world rejoiced. Live your life so that when you die, the world cries and you rejoice.
An interface between a strange intelligence and reality, it was made to serve as an epicenter between need and deeper understanding of impact.
Cunning and charming, Ulric was always on the prowl, that is until he lost his head.
A countermeasures specialist for the government, he built tools to break into systems to make them stronger, but the tools proved valuable in their own right.
No matter how warm it gets the trigger of this gun still seems oddly cold.

The world doesn't go to hell on its own. You gotta help it a bit.
As you wield this weapon you feel as though you're about to uncover a fundamental truth of the universe...
HM was a great Decker in the fifties. His Icon was a Fremen warrior from the Dune - movie from the eighties
To those who have fallen: Glenn, Russ, Dan. Thank you for the good times. I miss you.
If this was actually taken from a a Archangel isn't in question, the question is if they are still looking for it...
Have always had Loads of fun of Running shadowruns with my first ever created Noobsmurf the Dwarf
Crafted with love for a baby dragon.
Made when two minds came together. From different shadows, but born of the same light.
My children, to free us from pain our beloved Goddess has given her tears for us, rejoice!
Orichalcum focus crafted by an immortal elf enchanter.
Arteragorn Peridime, nicknamed Terry for short, had a sophisticated AI and camera put into this melee weapon so it would warn him of approaching enemies.
Freshly cleaned and pressed for full comfort and hygiene for runners on the go!
Death and destruction follow in the sword's wake whenever it is drawn.
With magic, the three facets of metahumanity (man, magic and machine) must be in balance if They are to be ended.

First of Madevil's luckiest night's. An "easy" run for ARES... though after scraping through: a case with AK-2078 in his hands.

This staff still echoes with the power of its former mistress - an elven martial arts prodigy.
faced with a vampire troll problem Wilk created the Zoanator, a super heavy pistol that fired sniper rounds

Used by Ch during La Revolutio...
